2697// FIXME-TABLE: more transient data could be stored in a stacked ImGuiTableTempData: e.g. SortSpecs, incoming RowData
2698// sizeof() ~ 580 bytes + heap allocs described in TableBeginInitMemory()
2699struct IMGUI_API ImGuiTable
2700{
2701 ImGuiID ID;
2702 ImGuiTableFlags Flags;
2703 void* RawData; // Single allocation to hold Columns[], DisplayOrderToIndex[] and RowCellData[]
2704 ImGuiTableTempData* TempData; // Transient data while table is active. Point within g.CurrentTableStack[]
2705 ImSpan<ImGuiTableColumn> Columns; // Point within RawData[]
2706 ImSpan<ImGuiTableColumnIdx> DisplayOrderToIndex; // Point within RawData[]. Store display order of columns (when not reordered, the values are 0...Count-1)
2707 ImSpan<ImGuiTableCellData> RowCellData; // Point within RawData[]. Store cells background requests for current row.
2708 ImBitArrayPtr EnabledMaskByDisplayOrder; // Column DisplayOrder -> IsEnabled map
2709 ImBitArrayPtr EnabledMaskByIndex; // Column Index -> IsEnabled map (== not hidden by user/api) in a format adequate for iterating column without touching cold data
2710 ImBitArrayPtr VisibleMaskByIndex; // Column Index -> IsVisibleX|IsVisibleY map (== not hidden by user/api && not hidden by scrolling/cliprect)
2711 ImGuiTableFlags SettingsLoadedFlags; // Which data were loaded from the .ini file (e.g. when order is not altered we won't save order)
2712 int SettingsOffset; // Offset in g.SettingsTables
2713 int LastFrameActive;
2714 int ColumnsCount; // Number of columns declared in BeginTable()
2715 int CurrentRow;
2716 int CurrentColumn;
2717 ImS16 InstanceCurrent; // Count of BeginTable() calls with same ID in the same frame (generally 0). This is a little bit similar to BeginCount for a window, but multiple table with same ID look are multiple tables, they are just synched.
2718 ImS16 InstanceInteracted; // Mark which instance (generally 0) of the same ID is being interacted with
2719 float RowPosY1;
2720 float RowPosY2;
2721 float RowMinHeight; // Height submitted to TableNextRow()
2722 float RowCellPaddingY; // Top and bottom padding. Reloaded during row change.
2723 float RowTextBaseline;
2724 float RowIndentOffsetX;
2725 ImGuiTableRowFlags RowFlags : 16; // Current row flags, see ImGuiTableRowFlags_
2726 ImGuiTableRowFlags LastRowFlags : 16;
2727 int RowBgColorCounter; // Counter for alternating background colors (can be fast-forwarded by e.g clipper), not same as CurrentRow because header rows typically don't increase this.
2728 ImU32 RowBgColor[2]; // Background color override for current row.
2729 ImU32 BorderColorStrong;
2730 ImU32 BorderColorLight;
2731 float BorderX1;
2732 float BorderX2;
2733 float HostIndentX;
2734 float MinColumnWidth;
2735 float OuterPaddingX;
2736 float CellPaddingX; // Padding from each borders. Locked in BeginTable()/Layout.
2737 float CellSpacingX1; // Spacing between non-bordered cells. Locked in BeginTable()/Layout.
2738 float CellSpacingX2;
2739 float InnerWidth; // User value passed to BeginTable(), see comments at the top of BeginTable() for details.
2740 float ColumnsGivenWidth; // Sum of current column width
2741 float ColumnsAutoFitWidth; // Sum of ideal column width in order nothing to be clipped, used for auto-fitting and content width submission in outer window
2742 float ColumnsStretchSumWeights; // Sum of weight of all enabled stretching columns
2743 float ResizedColumnNextWidth;
2744 float ResizeLockMinContentsX2; // Lock minimum contents width while resizing down in order to not create feedback loops. But we allow growing the table.
2745 float RefScale; // Reference scale to be able to rescale columns on font/dpi changes.
2746 float AngledHeadersHeight; // Set by TableAngledHeadersRow(), used in TableUpdateLayout()
2747 float AngledHeadersSlope; // Set by TableAngledHeadersRow(), used in TableUpdateLayout()
2748 ImRect OuterRect; // Note: for non-scrolling table, OuterRect.Max.y is often FLT_MAX until EndTable(), unless a height has been specified in BeginTable().
2749 ImRect InnerRect; // InnerRect but without decoration. As with OuterRect, for non-scrolling tables, InnerRect.Max.y is
2750 ImRect WorkRect;
2751 ImRect InnerClipRect;
2752 ImRect BgClipRect; // We use this to cpu-clip cell background color fill, evolve during the frame as we cross frozen rows boundaries
2753 ImRect Bg0ClipRectForDrawCmd; // Actual ImDrawCmd clip rect for BG0/1 channel. This tends to be == OuterWindow->ClipRect at BeginTable() because output in BG0/BG1 is cpu-clipped
2754 ImRect Bg2ClipRectForDrawCmd; // Actual ImDrawCmd clip rect for BG2 channel. This tends to be a correct, tight-fit, because output to BG2 are done by widgets relying on regular ClipRect.
2755 ImRect HostClipRect; // This is used to check if we can eventually merge our columns draw calls into the current draw call of the current window.
2756 ImRect HostBackupInnerClipRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->ClipRect during PushTableBackground()/PopTableBackground()
2757 ImGuiWindow* OuterWindow; // Parent window for the table
2758 ImGuiWindow* InnerWindow; // Window holding the table data (== OuterWindow or a child window)
2759 ImGuiTextBuffer ColumnsNames; // Contiguous buffer holding columns names
2760 ImDrawListSplitter* DrawSplitter; // Shortcut to TempData->DrawSplitter while in table. Isolate draw commands per columns to avoid switching clip rect constantly
2761 ImGuiTableInstanceData InstanceDataFirst;
2762 ImVector<ImGuiTableInstanceData> InstanceDataExtra; // FIXME-OPT: Using a small-vector pattern would be good.
2763 ImGuiTableColumnSortSpecs SortSpecsSingle;
2764 ImVector<ImGuiTableColumnSortSpecs> SortSpecsMulti; // FIXME-OPT: Using a small-vector pattern would be good.
2765 ImGuiTableSortSpecs SortSpecs; // Public facing sorts specs, this is what we return in TableGetSortSpecs()
2766 ImGuiTableColumnIdx SortSpecsCount;
2767 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ColumnsEnabledCount; // Number of enabled columns (<= ColumnsCount)
2768 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ColumnsEnabledFixedCount; // Number of enabled columns (<= ColumnsCount)
2769 ImGuiTableColumnIdx DeclColumnsCount; // Count calls to TableSetupColumn()
2770 ImGuiTableColumnIdx AngledHeadersCount; // Count columns with angled headers
2771 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBody; // Index of column whose visible region is being hovered. Important: == ColumnsCount when hovering empty region after the right-most column!
2772 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBorder; // Index of column whose right-border is being hovered (for resizing).
2773 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HighlightColumnHeader; // Index of column which should be highlighted.
2774 ImGuiTableColumnIdx AutoFitSingleColumn; // Index of single column requesting auto-fit.
2775 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ResizedColumn; // Index of column being resized. Reset when InstanceCurrent==0.
2776 ImGuiTableColumnIdx LastResizedColumn; // Index of column being resized from previous frame.
2777 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HeldHeaderColumn; // Index of column header being held.
2778 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ReorderColumn; // Index of column being reordered. (not cleared)
2779 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ReorderColumnDir; // -1 or +1
2780 ImGuiTableColumnIdx LeftMostEnabledColumn; // Index of left-most non-hidden column.
2781 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RightMostEnabledColumn; // Index of right-most non-hidden column.
2782 ImGuiTableColumnIdx LeftMostStretchedColumn; // Index of left-most stretched column.
2783 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RightMostStretchedColumn; // Index of right-most stretched column.
2784 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ContextPopupColumn; // Column right-clicked on, of -1 if opening context menu from a neutral/empty spot
2785 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeRowsRequest; // Requested frozen rows count
2786 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeRowsCount; // Actual frozen row count (== FreezeRowsRequest, or == 0 when no scrolling offset)
2787 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeColumnsRequest; // Requested frozen columns count
2788 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeColumnsCount; // Actual frozen columns count (== FreezeColumnsRequest, or == 0 when no scrolling offset)
2789 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RowCellDataCurrent; // Index of current RowCellData[] entry in current row
2790 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DummyDrawChannel; // Redirect non-visible columns here.
2791 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx Bg2DrawChannelCurrent; // For Selectable() and other widgets drawing across columns after the freezing line. Index within DrawSplitter.Channels[]
2792 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx Bg2DrawChannelUnfrozen;
2793 bool IsLayoutLocked; // Set by TableUpdateLayout() which is called when beginning the first row.
2794 bool IsInsideRow; // Set when inside TableBeginRow()/TableEndRow().
2795 bool IsInitializing;
2796 bool IsSortSpecsDirty;
2797 bool IsUsingHeaders; // Set when the first row had the ImGuiTableRowFlags_Headers flag.
2798 bool IsContextPopupOpen; // Set when default context menu is open (also see: ContextPopupColumn, InstanceInteracted).
2799 bool DisableDefaultContextMenu; // Disable default context menu contents. You may submit your own using TableBeginContextMenuPopup()/EndPopup()
2800 bool IsSettingsRequestLoad;
2801 bool IsSettingsDirty; // Set when table settings have changed and needs to be reported into ImGuiTableSetttings data.
2802 bool IsDefaultDisplayOrder; // Set when display order is unchanged from default (DisplayOrder contains 0...Count-1)
2803 bool IsResetAllRequest;
2804 bool IsResetDisplayOrderRequest;
2805 bool IsUnfrozenRows; // Set when we got past the frozen row.
2806 bool IsDefaultSizingPolicy; // Set if user didn't explicitly set a sizing policy in BeginTable()
2807 bool IsActiveIdAliveBeforeTable;
2808 bool IsActiveIdInTable;
2809 bool HasScrollbarYCurr; // Whether ANY instance of this table had a vertical scrollbar during the current frame.
2810 bool HasScrollbarYPrev; // Whether ANY instance of this table had a vertical scrollbar during the previous.
2811 bool MemoryCompacted;
2812 bool HostSkipItems; // Backup of InnerWindow->SkipItem at the end of BeginTable(), because we will overwrite InnerWindow->SkipItem on a per-column basis
2813
2814 ImGuiTable() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); LastFrameActive = -1; }
2815 ~ImGuiTable() { IM_FREE(RawData); }
2816};

2818// Transient data that are only needed between BeginTable() and EndTable(), those buffers are shared (1 per level of stacked table).
2819// - Accessing those requires chasing an extra pointer so for very frequently used data we leave them in the main table structure.

2830
2831 ImRect HostBackupWorkRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->WorkRect at the end of BeginTable()
2832 ImRect HostBackupParentWorkRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->ParentWorkRect at the end of BeginTable()
2833 ImVec2 HostBackupPrevLineSize; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.PrevLineSize at the end of BeginTable()
2834 ImVec2 HostBackupCurrLineSize; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.CurrLineSize at the end of BeginTable()
2835 ImVec2 HostBackupCursorMaxPos; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.CursorMaxPos at the end of BeginTable()
2836 ImVec1 HostBackupColumnsOffset; // Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ColumnsOffset at the end of BeginTable()
2837 float HostBackupItemWidth; // Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ItemWidth at the end of BeginTable()
2838 int HostBackupItemWidthStackSize;//Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ItemWidthStack.Size at the end of BeginTable()

2867// This is designed to be stored in a single ImChunkStream (1 header followed by N ImGuiTableColumnSettings, etc.)
2868struct ImGuiTableSettings
2869{

2881//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2882// [SECTION] ImGui internal API
2883// No guarantee of forward compatibility here!
2884//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2885
2886namespace ImGui
2887{
2888 // Windows
2889 // We should always have a CurrentWindow in the stack (there is an implicit "Debug" window)
2890 // If this ever crash because g.CurrentWindow is NULL it means that either
2891 // - ImGui::NewFrame() has never been called, which is illegal.
2892 // - You are calling ImGui functions after ImGui::EndFrame()/ImGui::Render() and before the next ImGui::NewFrame(), which is also illegal.
2893 inline ImGuiWindow* GetCurrentWindowRead(ImGuiContext* ctx) { ImGuiContext& g = *ctx; return g.CurrentWindow; }
2894 inline ImGuiWindow* GetCurrentWindow(ImGuiContext* ctx) { ImGuiContext& g = *ctx; g.CurrentWindow->WriteAccessed = true; return g.CurrentWindow; }

3075 inline bool IsNamedKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_NamedKey_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_NamedKey_END; }
3076 inline bool IsNamedKeyOrModKey(ImGuiKey key) { return (key >= ImGuiKey_NamedKey_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_NamedKey_END) || key == ImGuiMod_Ctrl || key == ImGuiMod_Shift || key == ImGuiMod_Alt || key == ImGuiMod_Super || key == ImGuiMod_Shortcut; }
3077 inline bool IsLegacyKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_LegacyNativeKey_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_LegacyNativeKey_END; }
3078 inline bool IsKeyboardKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Keyboard_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Keyboard_END; }
3079 inline bool IsGamepadKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Gamepad_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Gamepad_END; }
3080 inline bool IsMouseKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Mouse_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Mouse_END; }
3081 inline bool IsAliasKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Aliases_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Aliases_END; }
3082 inline ImGuiKeyChord ConvertShortcutMod(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKeyChord key_chord) { ImGuiContext& g = *ctx; IM_ASSERT_PARANOID(key_chord & ImGuiMod_Shortcut); return (key_chord & ~ImGuiMod_Shortcut) | (g.IO.ConfigMacOSXBehaviors ? ImGuiMod_Super : ImGuiMod_Ctrl); }
3083 inline ImGuiKey ConvertSingleModFlagToKey(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key)
3084 {
3085 ImGuiContext& g = *ctx;
3086 if (key == ImGuiMod_Ctrl) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModCtrl;
3087 if (key == ImGuiMod_Shift) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModShift;
3088 if (key == ImGuiMod_Alt) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModAlt;
3089 if (key == ImGuiMod_Super) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModSuper;
3090 if (key == ImGuiMod_Shortcut) return (g.IO.ConfigMacOSXBehaviors ? ImGuiKey_ReservedForModSuper : ImGuiKey_ReservedForModCtrl);
3091 return key;
3092 }

3106 // [EXPERIMENTAL] Low-Level: Key/Input Ownership
3107 // - The idea is that instead of "eating" a given input, we can link to an owner id.
3108 // - Ownership is most often claimed as a result of reacting to a press/down event (but occasionally may be claimed ahead).
3109 // - Input queries can then read input by specifying ImGuiKeyOwner_Any (== 0), ImGuiKeyOwner_None (== -1) or a custom ID.
3110 // - Legacy input queries (without specifying an owner or _Any or _None) are equivalent to using ImGuiKeyOwner_Any (== 0).
3111 // - Input ownership is automatically released on the frame after a key is released. Therefore:
3112 // - for ownership registration happening as a result of a down/press event, the SetKeyOwner() call may be done once (common case).
3113 // - for ownership registration happening ahead of a down/press event, the SetKeyOwner() call needs to be made every frame (happens if e.g. claiming ownership on hover).
3114 // - SetItemKeyOwner() is a shortcut for common simple case. A custom widget will probably want to call SetKeyOwner() multiple times directly based on its interaction state.
3115 // - This is marked experimental because not all widgets are fully honoring the Set/Test idioms. We will need to move forward step by step.
3116 // Please open a GitHub Issue to submit your usage scenario or if there's a use case you need solved.
3117 IMGUI_API ImGuiID GetKeyOwner(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key);
3118 IMGUI_API void SetKeyOwner(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3119 IMGUI_API void SetKeyOwnersForKeyChord(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKeyChord key, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3120 IMGUI_API void SetItemKeyOwner(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0); // Set key owner to last item if it is hovered or active. Equivalent to 'if (IsItemHovered() || IsItemActive()) { SetKeyOwner(key, GetItemID());'.
3121 IMGUI_API bool TestKeyOwner(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id); // Test that key is either not owned, either owned by 'owner_id'
3122 inline ImGuiKeyOwnerData* GetKeyOwnerData(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key) { if (key & ImGuiMod_Mask_) key = ConvertSingleModFlagToKey(ctx, key); IM_ASSERT(IsNamedKey(key)); return &ctx->KeysOwnerData[key - ImGuiKey_NamedKey_BEGIN]; }

3124 // [EXPERIMENTAL] High-Level: Input Access functions w/ support for Key/Input Ownership
3125 // - Important: legacy IsKeyPressed(ImGuiKey, bool repeat=true) _DEFAULTS_ to repeat, new IsKeyPressed() requires _EXPLICIT_ ImGuiInputFlags_Repeat flag.
3126 // - Expected to be later promoted to public API, the prototypes are designed to replace existing ones (since owner_id can default to Any == 0)
3127 // - Specifying a value for 'ImGuiID owner' will test that EITHER the key is NOT owned (UNLESS locked), EITHER the key is owned by 'owner'.
3128 // Legacy functions use ImGuiKeyOwner_Any meaning that they typically ignore ownership, unless a call to SetKeyOwner() explicitly used ImGuiInputFlags_LockThisFrame or ImGuiInputFlags_LockUntilRelease.
3129 // - Binding generators may want to ignore those for now, or suffix them with Ex() until we decide if this gets moved into public API.
3130 IMGUI_API bool IsKeyDown(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id);
3131 IMGUI_API bool IsKeyPressed(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0); // Important: when transitioning from old to new IsKeyPressed(): old API has "bool repeat = true", so would default to repeat. New API requiress explicit ImGuiInputFlags_Repeat.
3132 IMGUI_API bool IsKeyReleased(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id);
3133 IMGUI_API bool IsMouseDown(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiMouseButton button, ImGuiID owner_id);
3134 IMGUI_API bool IsMouseClicked(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiMouseButton button, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3135 IMGUI_API bool IsMouseReleased(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiMouseButton button, ImGuiID owner_id);
3136 IMGUI_API bool IsMouseDoubleClicked(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiMouseButton button, ImGuiID owner_id);

3138 // [EXPERIMENTAL] Shortcut Routing
3139 // - ImGuiKeyChord = a ImGuiKey optionally OR-red with ImGuiMod_Alt/ImGuiMod_Ctrl/ImGuiMod_Shift/ImGuiMod_Super.
3140 // ImGuiKey_C (accepted by functions taking ImGuiKey or ImGuiKeyChord)
3141 // ImGuiKey_C | ImGuiMod_Ctrl (accepted by functions taking ImGuiKeyChord)
3142 // ONLY ImGuiMod_XXX values are legal to 'OR' with an ImGuiKey. You CANNOT 'OR' two ImGuiKey values.
3143 // - When using one of the routing flags (e.g. ImGuiInputFlags_RouteFocused): routes requested ahead of time given a chord (key + modifiers) and a routing policy.
3144 // - Routes are resolved during NewFrame(): if keyboard modifiers are matching current ones: SetKeyOwner() is called + route is granted for the frame.
3145 // - Route is granted to a single owner. When multiple requests are made we have policies to select the winning route.
3146 // - Multiple read sites may use the same owner id and will all get the granted route.
3147 // - For routing: when owner_id is 0 we use the current Focus Scope ID as a default owner in order to identify our location.
3148 // - TL;DR;
3149 // - IsKeyChordPressed() compares mods + call IsKeyPressed() -> function has no side-effect.
3150 // - Shortcut() submits a route then if currently can be routed calls IsKeyChordPressed() -> function has (desirable) side-effects.
3151 IMGUI_API bool IsKeyChordPressed(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKeyChord key_chord, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3152 IMGUI_API bool Shortcut(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKeyChord key_chord, ImGuiID owner_id = 0, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3153 IMGUI_API bool SetShortcutRouting(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKeyChord key_chord, ImGuiID owner_id = 0, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3154 IMGUI_API bool TestShortcutRouting(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKeyChord key_chord, ImGuiID owner_id);
3155 IMGUI_API ImGuiKeyRoutingData* GetShortcutRoutingData(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKeyChord key_chord);
3156
3157 // [EXPERIMENTAL] Focus Scope
3158 // This is generally used to identify a unique input location (for e.g. a selection set)
3159 // There is one per window (automatically set in Begin), but:
3160 // - Selection patterns generally need to react (e.g. clear a selection) when landing on one item of the set.
3161 // So in order to identify a set multiple lists in same window may each need a focus scope.
3162 // If you imagine an hypothetical BeginSelectionGroup()/EndSelectionGroup() api, it would likely call PushFocusScope()/EndFocusScope()
3163 // - Shortcut routing also use focus scope as a default location identifier if an owner is not provided.
3164 // We don't use the ID Stack for this as it is common to want them separate.
3165 IMGUI_API void PushFocusScope(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiID id);
3166 IMGUI_API void PopFocusScope(ImGuiContext* ctx);
3167 inline ImGuiID GetCurrentFocusScope(ImGuiContext* ctx) { ImGuiContext& g = *ctx; return g.CurrentFocusScopeId; } // Focus scope we are outputting into, set by PushFocusScope()

3410 // Refactored focus/nav/tabbing system in 1.82 and 1.84. If you have old/custom copy-and-pasted widgets that used FocusableItemRegister():
3411 // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM < 18209: using 'ItemAdd(....)' and 'bool tab_focused = FocusableItemRegister(...)'
3412 // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18209: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemAddFlags_Focusable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Focused) != 0'
3413 // (New) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18413: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemFlags_Inputable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_FocusedTabbing) != 0 || (g.NavActivateId == id && (g.NavActivateFlags & ImGuiActivateFlags_PreferInput))' (WIP)
3414 // Widget code are simplified as there's no need to call FocusableItemUnregister() while managing the transition from regular widget to TempInputText()
3415 inline bool FocusableItemRegister(ImGuiWindow* window, ImGuiID id) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); IM_UNUSED(id); return false; } // -> pass ImGuiItemAddFlags_Inputable flag to ItemAdd()
3416 inline void FocusableItemUnregister(ImGuiWindow* window) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); } // -> unnecessary: TempInputText() uses ImGuiInputTextFlags_MergedItem
3417#endif
3418#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_OBSOLETE_KEYIO
3419 inline bool IsKeyPressedMap(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key, bool repeat = true) { IM_ASSERT(IsNamedKey(key)); return IsKeyPressed(ctx, key, repeat); } // Removed in 1.87: Mapping from named key is always identity!
3420#endif
